HEADWORD: Calmucks
<hw>Cal"mucks</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>; <sing><it>sing.</it>
<singw>Calmuck</singw>.</sing> <def>A branch of the Mongolian race
inhabiting parts of the Russian and Chinese empires; also
(<singf>sing.</singf>), the language of the Calmucks.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>Kalmucks</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

